googleReviewsBySlug.json.name: Areca Cooper
googleReviewsBySlug.json.text:
If I could give this business less than one star I would. This is the most unprofessional company I have ever experienced!!! Fence building is NOT their specialty so don’t even try to get that type of service. Don’t be fooled, they should have DECLINED the request! My mother should have known it was janky from the moment the owner wanted to charge to give her a quote! Usually a fence would take 2 days max to build out but this company took several. Most of that time was trying to figure out what to do! When they were finally questioned about the major gaps in the board the contractor got irate and quit on the job. When my mother asked about the deposit that she paid prior to them coming out they said nothing. Did not respond to the request of her receiving her deposit. They took 90% of the material that she paid for and quit 10% into the job. The level of unprofessionalism is WILD!  After they quit we had an inspection done because we needed someone to fix the terrible job that was done…. The inspector advised that the post/fence be knocked down due to:
1.) the spacing between the post
2.) The post weren’t in the ground far enough. (12 inches)
3.) The height of the fence was more than 6ft
4.) THE FENCE WAS OVER THE PROPERTY LINE!!!!

All of which was told to the contractor, when they were questioned about these issues the contractor quit! He was frustrated because he had to fix what he messed up. He did not check the property line before stating the job while the customer was out of town (which makes no sense!!). Why would you begin a job if you didn’t know where to place the fence?!?? That is CRAZY!  Now the customer is stuck paying someone to fix these issues on top of rebuilding the fence. The contractor is refusing to respond to the request for the return of the deposit. Bottom line STAY AWAY FROM THESE PEOPLE! VERY UNPROFESSIONAL, OVERPRICED, AND THE WORK IS TRASH!! 0/10 DO NOT RECOMMEND!!!!
googleReviewsBySlug.json.title: Jay's Home Improvement
